<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/10442144-anita"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1603510530i/10442144._UX100_CR0,43,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/10442144-anita">Anita</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The first book SHINJU begins in January 1689, i.e. Edo Genroku Period, Year 1, Month 12.<br/><br/>Genroku bunka or Genroku culture is the culture of the early E<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The first book SHINJU begins in January 1689, i.e. Edo Genroku Period, Year 1, Month 12.<br /><br />Genroku bunka or Genroku culture is the culture of the early Edo period (1603–1867), especially the Genroku era (1688–1704). Known as a period of luxurious display, the arts were increasingly patronized by a growing and powerful merchant class.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
